August 20, 2018

Second case study: "Wikipedia Pageview Data"

Data description:

  • 913 daily time series (Length of each time series: 394 - 6/1/2016 - 6/1/2017)

  • Five hierarchy groups:

  1. Agent (2 levels - user, spider)
  2. Access (3 levels - desktop, mobile-web, mobile-app)
  3. Purpose (9 levels - blogging related, business, gaming, general purpose, life style, photo sharing, reunion, travel, video)
  4. Language (4 levels - en (English), de (German), es (Spanish), zh (Chinese))

Six methods:

  1. Forecasting hierarchical time series using optimal combination reconciliation with arima bottom level forecast
  2. Forecasting hierarchical time series using optimal combination reconciliation with ets bottom level forecast
  3. Forecasting hierarchical time series using optimal combination reconciliation with OLS bottom level forecast
  4. Forecasting time series using arima models
  5. Forecasting time series using ets models
  6. Forecasting time series using OLS models

WikipediaData: Comparing all methods - with and without hierarchy - mean(log(RMSE))

Method Mean(log(RMSE))
arima -0.103
Hierarchy-arima -0.152
ets -0.45
Hierarchy-ets -0.408
OLS 0.092
Hierarchy-OLS 2.228
